                    Affiliation & Awards
                  






Affiliation





Scotts is Monsanto's exclusive agent for the international marketing and distribution of consumer Roundup® herbicide within the U.S. and most of Europe.
ScottsMiracle-Gro collaborates with Keep America Beautiful collaborate to create greater awareness of the environmental and social benefits of community green spaces by funding the development of public gardens in cities across the U.S.
The Scotts Miracle-Gro Company worked with Chesapeake Bay stakeholders to further protect the environmentally sensitive Chesapeake Bay water system by reformulating its lawn fertilizer products.









Awards





The Scotts Company's Web site, www.scotts.com, was named "Best General Interest Web Site" by the Web Marketing Association in its 2003 WebAward Competition.
In 2003, Wal*Mart named The Scotts Company "Supplier of the Year" in the lawn and garden category.
The Scotts Company was awarded the 2004 Environmental Technologies Award for the environmental benefits associated with the development of the Roundup FastAct™ Foam trigger-sprayer. The sprayer makes it easier to see where the product has been sprayed, reducing over-application.
In 2005, The Scotts Company was awarded the Home Safety Council's Commendation Seal for Safety Innovation in recognition of the safety features of Scotts' Pull 'n Spray® II applicator.





















